+# 0287 r16-r4-r1 — automatic Copilot advisory Issue comment
+
+## Finding
+
+The Projects workflow already produced the correlated request, advisory and
+manifest artifacts. The repository also already contained the pure v2 Issue
+comment planner and its controlled `gh` adapter. The missing wiring was inside
+the workflow: it never built the v2 preview and never invoked the publication
+adapter.
+
+## Change
+
+For every locally qualified inference dispatch with Copilot enabled, the
+workflow now:
+
+1. creates the three correlated artifacts;
+2. builds the existing v2 publication preview;
+3. plans the existing idempotent Issue comment;
+4. confirms that exact plan digest inside the same qualified workflow run;
+5. publishes and reads back the comment below the Issue;
+6. stores preview, plan and execution evidence with the manifest artifact.
+
+Artifact identity is built before publication. The three uploads use `always()`
+with file-existence guards, so a failed comment publication remains a failed run
+without destroying the artifacts needed for diagnosis and local recovery.
+
+The Issue body remains authoritative and unchanged. The comment is explicitly
+consultative. No laboratory execution, SQL write, Qdrant write or ProjectV2
+field mutation is introduced by this unit.
