+# Automatic Copilot Issue comment — 0287 r16-r4-r1
+
+```text
+ProjectV2 item enters the configured inference status
+  -> existing local transition dispatcher
+  -> workflow_dispatch(newicody/projects)
+  -> authoritative request + Copilot advisory + correlation manifest
+  -> human-readable artifact identity
+  -> existing v2 publication preview
+  -> existing deterministic Issue-comment plan
+  -> exact digest confirmation in the same qualified run
+  -> create or replay-noop below the source Issue
+  -> immediate readback
+  -> uploads always preserve artifacts and publication evidence
+```
+
+The local transition dispatcher remains the qualification boundary. The
+workflow does not add a broad `issues:` trigger because an Issue can exist
+without being selected for inference by ProjectV2.
+
+The Issue body is never rewritten. A visible comment is the primary GitHub
+surface for the first Copilot opinion. `Avis Copilot` is a secondary ProjectV2
+projection. Copilot remains untrusted and non-authoritative.
